<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-14T16:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-14T16:36:00-05:00" n="547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">125.61383/172: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-14T15:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            14, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received November 15, 10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>3275. Mrs. Jenkins has just telegraphed that her husband was
                                imprisoned in Puebla today. Jenkins and Mestre<note n="59" xml:id="d547fn59">Attorney for Mr. Jenkins.</note> report that
                                evidence on which arrest was made is false and was extracted from
                                persons testifying by threats of death.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>